{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/binance/binance-connector-python/pulls/179", "id": 1103059974, "node_id": "PR_kwDOD1Qhrs5Bv1wG", "html_url": "https://github.com/binance/binance-connector-python/pull/179", "diff_url": "https://github.com/binance/binance-connector-python/pull/179.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/binance/binance-connector-python/pull/179.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/binance/binance-connector-python/issues/179", "number": 179, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "Fix reactor stop hang", "user": {"login": "EliaOnceAgain", "id": 35046248, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM1MDQ2MjQ4", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/35046248?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/EliaOnceAgain", "html_url": "https://github.com/EliaOnceAgain", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/EliaOnceAgain/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/EliaOnceAgain/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/EliaOnceAgain/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/EliaOnceAgain/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/EliaOnceAgain/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/EliaOnceAgain/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/EliaOnceAgain/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/EliaOnceAgain/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/EliaOnceAgain/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "body": "Twisted reactor not exiting cleanly. Encountered while running pytest, which does not exit after all tests are finished. Reproduction steps below.\r\n\r\nUbuntu 22.04.1 LTS\r\nPython 3.10.6\r\nbinance-connector==1.18.0\r\nTwisted==22.8.0\r\npytest==7.2.0\r\n\r\nFrom: [Invoking Twisted From Other Threads](https://docs.twisted.org/en/twisted-18.7.0/core/howto/threading.html#invoking-twisted-from-other-threads)\r\n> Methods within Twisted may only be invoked from the reactor thread unless otherwise noted... This means that if you start a thread and call a Twisted method, you might get correct behavior… or you might get _hangs_, crashes, or corrupted data. So don’t do it.\r\n\r\nTest case:\r\n```\r\nimport pytest\r\nfrom binance.spot import Spot\r\nfrom binance.websocket.spot.websocket_client import SpotWebsocketClient as WebsocketClient\r\n\r\n\r\nclass TestBinanceAPI:\r\n    @pytest.fixture(scope=\"class\")\r\n    def ws_client(self):\r\n        client = WebsocketClient()\r\n        client.start()\r\n        yield client\r\n        client.stop()\r\n\r\n    def test_hello_world(self, ws_client):\r\n        assert ws_client\r\n```\r\n\r\nExpected outcome:\r\nTest finishes successfully, `pytest` exists gracefully at the end.\r\n\r\nActual outcome:\r\nTest finishes successfully, `pytest` hangs indefinitely\r\n\r\n# Pre fix output\r\n```\r\n> /my-path/tests/test_wsclient.py(12)ws_client()\r\n-> client.stop()\r\n> /my-venv/lib/python3.10/site-packages/binance/websocket/websocket_client.py(15)stop()\r\n-> reactor.stop()\r\n\r\n(Pdb) ll\r\n 10         def stop(self):\r\n 11             try:\r\n 12                 self.close()\r\n 13             finally:\r\n 14                 import pdb; pdb.set_trace()\r\n 15  ->            reactor.stop()\r\n(Pdb) reactor._stopped\r\nFalse\r\n(Pdb) reactor.running\r\nTrue\r\n(Pdb) n\r\n--Return--\r\n> /my-env/lib/python3.10/site-packages/binance/websocket/websocket_client.py(15)stop()->None\r\n-> reactor.stop()\r\n(Pdb) reactor.running\r\nTrue <<<<<<< Still true\r\n(Pdb) reactor._stopped\r\nTrue <<<<<<< Changed to true, yet still running\r\n(Pdb) continue\r\n```\r\n\r\nAt this point, pytest hangs, never exits or gives up control of the command line. Last printed logline:\r\n```============================================================================= 1 passed in 124.56s (0:02:04) ==============================================================================```\r\n\r\n# Post fix output\r\n```\r\n-> reactor.callFromThread(reactor.stop)\r\n(Pdb) ll\r\n 10         def stop(self):\r\n 11             try:\r\n 12                 self.close()\r\n 13             finally:\r\n 14                 import pdb; pdb.set_trace()\r\n 15                 # reactor.stop()\r\n 16  ->             reactor.callFromThread(reactor.stop)\r\n(Pdb) reactor._stopped\r\nFalse\r\n(Pdb) reactor.running\r\nTrue\r\n(Pdb) n\r\n--Return--\r\n> /my-env/lib/python3.10/site-packages/binance/websocket/websocket_client.py(16)stop()->None\r\n-> reactor.callFromThread(reactor.stop)\r\n(Pdb) reactor._stopped\r\nTrue\r\n(Pdb) reactor.running\r\nFalse <<<<< correctly changed\r\n(Pdb) continue\r\n```\r\nAt this point, pytest finishes successfully, exits gracefully, and returns command line control to the caller.", "created_at": "2022-10-28T12:41:07Z", "updated_at": "2024-01-03T23:00:27Z", "closed_at": "2022-12-14T05:38:46Z", "merged_at": "2022-12-14T05:38:46Z", "merge_commit_sha": "33364b1ea9d12fbd8ede6ee3b0ace3358ad74957", "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "requested_reviewers": [{"login": "2pd", "id": 365354, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM2NTM1NA==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/365354?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/2pd", "html_url": "https://github.com/2pd", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/2pd/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/2pd/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/2pd/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/2pd/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/2pd/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/2pd/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/2pd/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/2pd/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/2pd/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": 